      "message": "Jenkins isn\u0027t a repository, and we should archive artifacts to it.\nIt\u0027s good for keeping results, with a pinch of salt, that they are just current builds.\n\nSee some blog posts about the risks of doing it at:\nhttps://blog.inedo.com/jenkins/dont-store-build-artifacts-in-jenkins\n\nWhat about checking them back into the repository instead by creating a change back to the repository, if the file has changed since the last build?",
